## Quick start

### 1 — Create your `.env`

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env:
#   AZURE_IOT_HUB_NAME=myhub          ← without .azure-devices.net
#   AZURE_DEVICE_ID=my-opc-device
```

### 2 — Generate certificates

```bash
chmod +x scripts/generate_certs.sh
./scripts/generate_certs.sh
```

This creates `certs/device.crt`, `certs/device.key`, and downloads
`certs/azure_root_ca.pem` (DigiCert Global Root G2).

> **Important:** The script prints the `az` CLI commands needed to register
> the Root CA and the device in IoT Hub. Run those before continuing.

### 3 — Register the Root CA in Azure IoT Hub

```bash
# Upload CA certificate
az iot hub certificate create \
  --hub-name $AZURE_IOT_HUB_NAME \
  --name root-ca-cert \
  --path certs/root_ca.crt

# Proof-of-possession (follow the prompts from generate_certs.sh output)
# See: https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/iot-hub/tutorial-x509-scripts
```

### 4 — Register the device

```bash
az iot hub device-identity create \
  --hub-name $AZURE_IOT_HUB_NAME \
  --device-id $AZURE_DEVICE_ID \
  --auth-method x509_ca
```

### 5 — Build and run

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

To run only the publisher or subscriber:

```bash
docker compose up --build publisher
docker compose up subscriber
```

